## Content Management

### Content Structure
- All text content in `src/config/content.ts`
- Support for English (`englishContent`) and Chinese (`zhContent`)
- Dynamic content selection based on URL path (`/zh-tw`)

### Course Data Pattern
```typescript
courses: {
  "course-id": {
    title: string;
    description: string;
    instructor: string;
    rating: number;
    ratingNum: number;
    duration: string;
    level: "Beginner" | "Intermediate" | "Advanced";
    features: string[];
    whatYouWillLearn: string[];
    curriculum: CurriculumSection[];
    reviews?: Review[];
    video?: string;
  }
}
```

## Navigation Patterns

### Course URLs
- English: `/course/ai-for-finance-professionals`
- Chinese: `/zh-tw/course/ai-for-finance-professionals`
- Hash links for main page sections: `#why-join`, `#online-courses`

### Link Handling
- Use `<a href="">` for hash links and external navigation
- Use `<Link to="">` for React Router navigation
- Use `window.location.assign()` for forced navigation with hash

## Component Patterns

### SEO with React Helmet
```tsx
<Helmet>
  <title>{dynamicTitle}</title>
  <meta name="description" content={dynamicDescription} />
  <link rel="canonical" href={canonicalUrl} />
</Helmet>
```

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Use `hidden md:flex` for desktop-only elements
- Use `flex-col sm:flex-row` for responsive layouts

### Animations
- Use `transition-all duration-300` for smooth transitions
- Use `group` and `group-hover:` for hover effects
- Use `animate-fade-in` for entrance animations

## Performance Guidelines
- Lazy load images with proper alt text
- Use `backdrop-blur-sm` for glassmorphism effects
- Optimize images: use appropriate sizes and formats
- Use `useEffect` for side effects like scrolling

## Accessibility
- Proper semantic HTML structure
- Alt text for all images
- Keyboard navigation support
- Screen reader friendly text
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)

## Internationalization
- Chinese content inherits from English: `...englishContent`
- Override specific fields for Chinese translations
- Maintain same data structure for both languages
- Use proper Chinese typography and spacing
- Files for Chinese content goes under /zh-tw
- Every Chinese page must have a corresponding English page